<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>
<Patch>
	
		<Operation Class="PatchOperationSequence">
			<success>Normal</success>
			<operations>
				
			<li Class="PatchOperationAdd">
				<xpath>/Defs/XmlExtensions.SettingsMenuDef[defName = "FrozenSnowFoxTweaksSettings"]/settings/li[tag="FrozenSnowFoxTweaksVehicleFramework"]/settings</xpath>
				<value>

			
						
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
				<text>Vehicle Framework Tweaks</text>
				<font>Medium</font>
				<anchor>Middle</anchor>
				<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkTweaksTitle</tKey>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine">
			</li>
					
			<!-- Factions Stock Vehicle Parts -->
					
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
				<label>Factions Stock Vehicle Parts</label>
				<key>FSFVehicleFrameworkFactionsStockVehiclePartsOn</key>
				<defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
				<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkFactionsStockVehiclePartsTitle</tKey>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor">
				<color>(163,177,188)</color>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
				<text>Adds an additional stock of Vehicle Parts to tech appropriate Faction bases based on an input range.</text>
				<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkFactionsStockVehiclePartsOnDesc</tKey>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor"/>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.ToggleableSettings">
				<key>FSFVehicleFrameworkFactionsStockVehiclePartsOn</key>
				<caseTrue>
					<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor">
						<color>(163,177,188)</color>
					</li>
					<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Numeric">
						<key>FSFVehicleFrameworkFactionsStockVehiclePartsMin</key>
						<defaultValue>5</defaultValue>
						<min>1</min>
						<max>100</max>
						<label>Vehicle Parts Stock Minimum Range</label>
						<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkFactionsStockVehiclePartsMin</tKey>
					</li>					
					<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Numeric">
						<key>FSFVehicleFrameworkFactionsStockVehiclePartsMax</key>
						<defaultValue>10</defaultValue>
						<min>1</min>
						<max>100</max>
						<label>Vehicle Parts Stock Maximum Range</label>
						<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkFactionsStockVehiclePartsMax</tKey>
					</li>
					<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
						<text>Adds an additional stock of Vehicle Parts to tech appropriate Faction bases based on an input range.\nDefault setting 5-10.</text>
						<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkFactionsStockVehiclePartsDesc</tKey>
					</li>
					<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor"/>
				</caseTrue>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine">
				<spacing>12</spacing>
			</li>
					
			<!-- Faster Helicopters -->
			
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
				<label>Faster Helicopters</label>
				<key>FSFVehicleFrameworkFasterHelicopters</key>
				<defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
				<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkFasterHelicoptersTitle</tKey>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor">
				<color>(163,177,188)</color>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
				<text>Speeds up the takeoff and landing animation on helicopters that are slow to use.  For example this tweak changes the takeoff and landing animation speed on Vanilla Expanded Helicopters so they take one third of the time making them comparable in speed to drop pod style vehicles like the Toad.</text>
				<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkFasterHelicoptersDesc</tKey>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor"/>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine">
				<spacing>12</spacing>
			</li>
			
			<!-- Faster Vehicles -->
			
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
				<label>Faster Vehicles</label>
				<key>FSFVehicleFrameworkFasterVehiclesOn</key>
				<defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
				<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkFasterVehiclesTitle</tKey>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor">
				<color>(163,177,188)</color>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
				<text>Allows you to multiply the speed of all land and water vehicles on the world map by an input value.</text>
				<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkFasterVehiclesOnDesc</tKey>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor"/>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.ToggleableSettings">
				<key>FSFVehicleFrameworkFasterVehiclesOn</key>
				<caseTrue>
					<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor">
						<color>(163,177,188)</color>
					</li>
					<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Slider">
						<key>FSFVehicleFrameworkFasterVehicles</key>
						<defaultValue>2.0</defaultValue>
						<min>1.0</min>
						<max>10.0</max>
						<decimals>1</decimals>
						<label>Speed Multiplier {FSFVehicleFrameworkFasterVehicles}</label>
						<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkFasterVehicles</tKey>
					</li>
					<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
						<text>Move the slider to adjust the speed multiplier of all land and water Vehicles on the world map.  The value is a straight multiplier, a value of 2 will double the original while 3 will triple it.\nThe Vanilla value is 1.</text>
						<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkFasterVehiclesDesc</tKey>
					</li>
					<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor"/>
				</caseTrue>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine">
				<spacing>12</spacing>
			</li>
					
			<!-- Rename Car Parts -->
			
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Checkbox">
				<label>Rename Car Parts</label>
				<key>FSFVehicleFrameworkRenameCarParts</key>
				<defaultValue>false</defaultValue>
				<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkRenameCarPartsTitle</tKey>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor">
				<color>(163,177,188)</color>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.Text">
				<text>Changes the name of Car Parts from Vanilla Vehicles Expanded to Vehicle Parts.</text>
				<tKey>FSFTweaksVehicleFrameworkRenameCarPartsDesc</tKey>
			</li>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.SetColor"/>
			<li Class="XmlExtensions.Setting.GapLine">
			</li>
						
				
					
				</value>
			</li>
				
			</operations>
		</Operation>
	
</Patch>